# i18n & messages

## Namespaces

One top-level key per app in `messages/en.json` (camelCase): `bitScope`, `noiseMeterShusher`,  `zuliCollage`, etc.

Typical keys: `hero`, `download`, `privacy`, `terms`, `footer`, `features`, …

## Legal sections

```json
"privacy": {
  "title": "Privacy Policy",
  "lastUpdated": "Last updated: May 2026",
  "intro": "...",
  "section1": { "title": "...", "content": "...", "items": ["..."] },
  "sectionContact": { "title": "Contact", "email": "zuki.apps.dev@gmail.com", "address": "..." }
}
```

Wire in page with `LegalSections` — pass `sections`, `listSectionKeys`, `withContent2`, `contactSectionKey`.

## Locales

- `i18n.ts` deep-merges `{locale}.json` over `en.json`
- For new apps, **en.json only** is often sufficient (other locales inherit)
- `dreambitLegacy` loaded separately — do not nest under app keys

## Pitfalls

- Invalid JSON or missing nested keys → runtime 500 in prod; always mirror section keys used in `page.tsx`
- Reformatting entire `en.json` creates huge diffs — patch surgically
